By @grillhunters 
.
Have you ever had a grilled romaine salad before? If not, you’re in for a unique and delicious smoky surprise.

Here’s a list of ingredients for the marinade and salad. Full recipe with instruction is on the blog.

// Garlic & herbs marinade //
- 3/4 cup olive oil
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tbsp basil, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp chives, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp rosemary, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp parsley, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp lemon zest
- 3 garlic cloves, minced
- 1/2 tsp chili powder
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp black pepper

// Grilles Romaine Salad //
- 1 heart romaine lettuce cut in half lengthwise 
- ½ cup Parmesan cheese flakes
- 4 slice bacon grilled and crispy
- 4 tbsp olive oil extra virgin
- 1 tbsp kosher salt
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tsp back pepper
- ½ lemon zest

from Scratch! 🇲🇦😍🍆🍅🔥
This dish is a must and the flavors are amazing!
🕌: Fez, Morocco
🎥: @foodyfetish #foodyfetishoriginal 
Tag a Friend that would love this dish!👇🏼
.

Ingredients
* 1 large eggplant (peeled and chopped*)
* 4 large tomatoes (peeled, seeded and chopped)
* 3 cloves of garlic (finely chopped or pressed)
* 1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro and parsley (mixed)
* 1 tablespoon paprika
* 1 tablespoon cumin
* 1 1/2 teaspoons salt
* 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)
* 1/4 cup olive oil
* 1/3 cup water
* Small wedge of lemon (optional)

To Make the Zaalouk:
* Mix all ingredients in a large, deep skillet or pot. Cover and simmer over medium to medium-high heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Adjust the heat if necessary to avoid burning the zaalouk.  Use a spoon or potato masher to crush and blend the tomatoes and eggplant. If you like, a small wedge of lemon can be added to the pan at this time. Continue simmering, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until the liquids are reduced and the zaalouk can be stirred into a heap in the center of the pan.

Who needs a delicious dinner idea for tonight? 🙋‍♀️🍽 

Baked Honey Mustard Salmon recipe is so easy to make and ready to serve in just under 30 minutes. 

This salmon filet recipe by @healthyfitnessmeals is so healthy, moist, delicious, and oven-baked to perfection. Perfect for a busy weeknight dinner. 

📝Ingredients
1 pound salmon fillet skin-on
1 large lemon
1 tbsp. finely chopped fresh parsley optional for garnishing 1 tbsp. coconut oil melted 2 tbsp. honey 3 tbsp. whole Dijon mustard 2 tbsp. lemon juice 1/2 tsp. kosher salt or to taste 1/4 tsp. freshly ground black pepper or to taste

🧑‍🍳 Instructions
1. Preheat the oven to 375°F.

2. Whisk all the sauce ingredients to a bowl and set aside. Slice the lemon into thin rounds and finely chop the parsley. 
3. Add a layer of sliced lemon into a baking dish. Place the salmon on top. 
4. Pour 2/3rd of the sauce over the salmon. Rub until well coated. Bake for 12 minutes, or until salmon is cooked through. 
5. Pour the remaining 1/3rd cup of the sauce and broil for about 2-3 minutes more, until nicely golden brown. 
6. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve.

#salmon #salmondinner #dinner #healthyeats #fishdinner #mediterraneandiet #mediterraneanfood #lemons #nutrition #dietplan

Grilled Flank Steak, Charred Sweet Potatoes, Broccolini, Pattypan Squash & Chimichurri… 

Feel free to switch things up with what you like. Substitute chicken, pork chops, lamb chops, venison backstraps or seafood…By @primal_gourmet

Grill some zucchini, eggplant, peppers, onions, or okra. You’re the boss, applesauce!

For Chimichurri:
1⁄2 cup boiling water
1 teaspoon kosher salt
1⁄2 cup finely chopped fresh parsley leaves
1⁄2 cup finely chopped fresh cilantro leaves
1⁄4 cup red wine vinegar
1⁄4 cup extra-virgin olive oil
1 shallot, finely chopped
8 to 10 fresh mint leaves, finely chopped
1 garlic clove, finely chopped or mashed to a paste
1 teaspoon dried oregano
1 teaspoon red pepper flakes, or 1 fresh red chile, finely chopped
1 teaspoon smoked Spanish paprika
.
For Steak & Veggies:
3-4 sweet potatoes
1.5 pound flank steak
Kosher salt & pepper
Avocado oil
1 bunch broccolini
3-4 pattypan squash, halved
.
For Chimichurri: In a medium bowl, combine the boiling water & salt. Stir until dissolved, about 30 seconds, & let water cool to room temp. Add the remaining ingredients & stir to combine. Cover & refrigerate up to 2 weeks.
.
For Steak & Veggies:
1. Preheat Traeger to 500F. Place sweet potatoes directly on grill towards the back. Cook, turning every 15 min, until charred & completely fork-tender, around 45 min total depending on size. 

2. Drizzle steak with avocado oil & liberally season both sides with salt & pepper. Massage to coat & set aside at room temp for one hour. Drizzle broccolini & squash with avocado oil & season with salt & pepper. 

3. Place the steak towards the front or back of the Traeger & grill, undisturbed, until grill marks form, around 6 minutes. Flip & cook until internal temperature is around 135F for medium rare, around 3 more minutes. Veggies can go along either side perimeter. Cook until charred and tender, around 8 minutes total. 

4. Let steak rest 8 minutes before carving & serving with chimichurri & veggies. 

#sweetpotatoes #sweetpotato #steak

Omg look at these beauties😍😍🥗 by @nocrumbsleft which would be your favorite? 1,2,3 or 4? Comment below👇
-
✔️ SAVE this Post to make later
✔️ TAG a friend who needs this #healthyeating inspo
✔️ FOLLOW @healthy.foodyss for daily #healthyeating inspo & recipes from across the gram
-
📸 + below deets by @nocrumbsleft
-
1️⃣🥩🥗Steak Salad: Here I have coated the outside with freshly ground black pepper, but leave it off if you prefer. The Creamy Horseradish Dressing is perfect as a dressing or served on the side as a dipping sauce with vegetables. Gooey eggs, pepperoncini, and avocado take it to the next level. Plus, of course, my Marinated Onions.
2️⃣🎣 🥗Salmon Plate: Start with salmon or any fish you love, cut into large fingers. Sear for about three minutes or so a side. Here I’ve added blanched green beans, sweet potato crisps, pear tomatoes, and slices of cucumbers. I love this time of year with the hint of spring, and it makes me want to eat all kinds of green vegetables. Remember, a salad is only as good as your ingredients, which is why I like to cook with local and in season. This is topped off with my Marinated Red Onions. 
3️⃣🥓🥗Quick Crab Cobb Salad: Bacon, hunks of avocado, cucumber, small pear tomatoes, tossed in a mandarin orange vinaigrette. Pick up your seafood from the fish store or grocery store, and while the bacon is cooking make your simple vinaigrette and cut your vegetables. As the bacon comes out of the oven, assemble your salad and drizzle with my delicious vinaigrette. So simple, so delicious, so soul satisfying. Keep it Whole30 or take it up a notch and add some sheep’s milk feta: delish!
4️⃣ 🍤🥗Shrimp Platter: Marinated shrimp, sweet potato crisps, gorgeous Greens, all kinds of crunchy goodness and of course my Marinated Red Onions, will make you want to eat this salad on repeat pretty much everyday!
